<p>I would like to defend the anonymous writer. I think there is a lot to be said about dealing with what a writer is saying as opposed to focusing on who is saying it. Many an ad hominem attack arises from one person knowing something about another. It helps to know who is writing what, but it&#8217;s not an ethical principle wether or not you reveal your actual identity, it is merely a method. Anonymity protects meaning and can help in avoiding personal attacks. </p>

